<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="574" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1291,2002]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1940,1966]" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name 
<taxonomicName authorityName="F.Walker" authorityYear="1869" box="[546,656,1939,1965]" class="Insecta" family="Dryophthoridae" genus="Conocephalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="574" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="latipennis">
<emphasis box="[546,656,1939,1965]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="574">latipennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a combination of the Latin “lata” and “penn”, indicating broad tegmen.
</paragraph>
